@startuml
title POST /api/v1/users — Error Paths
autonumber

actor Client
participant "create_user()" as View
participant "IsTeacherOrAbove" as Perm
participant "can_create_user()" as RoleGate
participant "identifier_in_use()" as DupCheck
database Postgres

== Error: Not teacher or above (403) ==
Client -> View: POST /users {role: "STUDENT"}\n[JWT: student user]
View -> Perm: has_permission(request)
Perm -> Perm: is_staff? No\nhas RESEARCHER? No\nhas TEACHER? No
Perm --x Client: 403 Forbidden (DRF)

== Error: Admin tries to create STUDENT (403) ==
Client -> View: POST /users\n{role: "ROLE_STUDENT", name: "..."}\n[JWT: admin]
View -> Perm: has_permission -> True
View -> RoleGate: can_create_user(admin, STUDENT)
RoleGate -> RoleGate: admin can only create\nRESEARCHER or TEACHER
RoleGate --> View: False
View --x Client: 403 "Forbidden"

== Error: Teacher tries to create TEACHER (403) ==
Client -> View: POST /users\n{role: "ROLE_TEACHER", ...}\n[JWT: teacher]
View -> RoleGate: can_create_user(teacher, TEACHER)
RoleGate -> RoleGate: teacher can only\ncreate STUDENT
RoleGate --> View: False
View --x Client: 403 "Forbidden"

== Error: Username in request body (400) ==
Client -> View: POST /users\n{username: "custom", name: "..."}
View -> View: "username" in request.data
View --x Client: 400 "username is system-managed..."

== Error: Missing name (400) ==
Client -> View: POST /users\n{email: "...", role: "ROLE_TEACHER"}
View -> View: name not present
View --x Client: 400 "name is required"

== Error: Non-student without email (400) ==
Client -> View: POST /users\n{name: "...", role: "ROLE_TEACHER"}\n(no email)
View -> View: role != STUDENT and no email
View --x Client: 400 "email is required for\nnon-student accounts"

== Error: Email already taken (400) ==
Client -> View: POST /users\n{name: "...", email: "taken@...",\nrole: "ROLE_TEACHER"}
View -> DupCheck: identifier_in_use("taken@...")
DupCheck -> Postgres: SELECT EXISTS app_users\nWHERE email = ?
Postgres --> DupCheck: True
DupCheck --> View: True
View --x Client: 400 "Email already taken"
@enduml
